Bring a large pain of water to the boil. Add a pinch of salt and the greens to the boiling water. Cook for 2 minutes, then drain and rinse under cold wate. Drain thoroughly.Heat the oil in a large frying pan over a high heat. Add the chopped bacon and fry for 3-4 minutes, stirring regularly, until the fat has melted and the bacon is crisp and golden-brown.Add the cooked spring greens to the pan and stir-fry for 1-2 minutes, or until wilted and coated in the fat. Season with salt and pepper and stir in the nuts. Serve immediately.